      "https://purl.org/hed#HedTag"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "EEG rhythm at 7-11 Hz composed of arch-shaped waves occurring over the central or centro-parietal regions of the scalp during wakefulness. Amplitudes varies but is mostly below 50 microV. Blocked or attenuated most clearly by contralateral movement, thought of movement, readiness to move or tactile stimulation."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
